  "body": "I noticed the rook-operator running master-latest (v0.3.1-99-gea2b435) had crashed a few times in the past couple hours:\r\n```\r\n> kubectl get pod\r\nNAME                             READY     STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE\r\nrook-operator-1641293690-h77mx   1/1       Running   3          2h\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe logs show the reason for the crash:\r\n```\r\n> kubectl logs --previous=true rook-operator-1641293690-h77mx\r\n<ommitted>\r\n2017-04-28 02:17:56.987758 W | operator: cancelling cluster tpr watch. failed to poll cluster event. EOF\r\n2017-04-28 02:17:56.988055 E | operator: failed to watch clusters. received invalid event from API server: failed to poll cluster event. EOF\r\n2017-04-28 02:17:56.988136 I | op-cluster: Stopping monitoring of cluster rook in namespace rook\r\npanic: close of closed channel\r\n\r\ngoroutine 86 [running]:\r\ngithub.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator.(*clusterManager).stopTrack(0xc4200cfe60, 0xc42040c3c0)\r\n\t/home/rook/go/src/github.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator/cluster.go:128 +0x1a1\r\ngithub.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator.(*clusterManager).startCluster.func1(0xc4200cfe60, 0xc42040c3c0)\r\n\t/home/rook/go/src/github.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator/cluster.go:186 +0x2e7\r\ncreated by github.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator.(*clusterManager).startCluster\r\n\t/home/rook/go/src/github.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator/cluster.go:186 +0x20c\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that a very similar event happens for the pool TPR (EOF), but we recover from that one OK:\r\n```\r\n2017-04-28 02:01:12.361612 E | operator: failed to watch rook pool tpr. received invalid event from API server: failed to poll pool event. EOF. retrying...\r\n2017-04-28 02:01:18.362424 I | operator: finding existing pools...\r\n2017-04-28 02:01:18.366234 I | operator: found 1 pools. ensuring they exist.\r\n2017-04-28 02:01:18.366317 I | operator: checking pool replicapool in namespace rook\r\n2017-04-28 02:01:18.376719 I | op-cluster: pool replicapool already exists in namespace rook \r\n2017-04-28 02:01:18.376790 I | operator: start watching pool tpr in namespace rook: 11451\r\n```",
